Point-cloud stitching is currently performed only after the scan operation has completed. During individual scan passes, the IPC is often idle, which creates an opportunity to perform stitching asynchronously in the background. By stitching completed scan passes while later passes are still running, we can distribute the workload across the scan sequence and reduce the amount of stitching required at the end. This should lower post-scan processing time and improve overall throughput without impacting active scan acquisition.